  "texts": [
    "Moreover, the disparity from the solutions obtained using optimized parameters is reduced by a factor of three (from 3.6 p.p. to 1.0 p.p.)",
    "when the edge weights are drawn from the exponential distribution, and by a factor of ≈ 6 with the Cauchy distribution (from 20.7 to 3.3 p.p.",
    ").We then propose a heuristic parameter rescaling rule for QAOA on arbitrary weighted problems.",
    "The heuristic rule is inspired by the theoretical results for the weighted MaxCut problem.",
    "As an example highlighting the generality of our observations, we consider QAOA applied to a portfolio optimization problem with a budget constraint, where the constraint is enforced throughout the QAOA evolution by the xy Hamming-weight-preserving mixer."
